content.text: My hope too.    Today's early volume and CC confirms to me that astute larger investors are not going to let the train powered by tubes leave them out of 1'st class.  We as small investors always have to wait for that volume from institutions that see the long term value and destination.   So getting in early as individuals it seems we can enjoy the ride.

Semi sales were at $40 million plus in good years. Last year they were at around $20 million. CC indicated the semi's customers expect their best year ever in 25. So like I said it was an OK quarter with the prospects for an outstanding year upcoming from their semi business and great prospects in GES and PMT markets. It will be a $20 stock sometime in 25 IMO.

Less than stellar performance. Once again anyone who thinks RELL performance was even "ok" is setting a really low bar.Note - Inventory levels - when do the writeoffs happen? Have they taken reserves?Management is a misnomer...

Glad to hear about the global repowering and Europe.  My understanding is that Europe is much more focused on drastic reduction in fossil fuel use.  Here, we have the one party in power that was supposed to deliver major reductions.  Instead we extract and export more than ever, and this All Of Above, has meant more and more climate change for the big picture/world.   With the threat of more pragmatic delay and deceit from Democrats the all out Burn Baby Burn/replacing Drill Baby Drill from the other party, all means Europe will have to carry the faster transition to Green Energy until our two parties are refunded or Ameicans can demand a refocus as Democrats once promised.   Mention this with hope RELL partners with a company like Emeron Group that is making tremendous progress in Europe and even France where regulatory market is demanding but Emeron is opening up the market there too.

An OK quarter announced. I think the forward looking prospects for their semiconductor business might be the key in tomorrow's conference call. If they begin to approach the sales of fiscal 23 in their semi business I think we will see new 52 week highs in RELL.

Earnings tomorrow and conference call Thursday morning. Unfortunately RELL still doesn't look like they unloaded their Health Care Division and thus it most likely had to face additional losses from that division in the quarter. Hoping for the best thinking the worst.
